name: 3M
industry: Manufacturing, Industrial, Healthcare, Consumer Goods, Electronics, Safety
summary: 3M Company is an American multinational conglomerate operating in the fields of industry, worker safety, and consumer goods.

name: A-Mark Precious Metals
summary: A-Mark Precious Metals is a precious metals trading company. It was the first company allowed to make and sell coins from the metals recovered in the shipwreck of SS Gairsoppa. A-Mark is traded on Nasdaq and is a Fortune 500 company as of 2021.

name: A.O. Smith
summary: A. O. Smith Corporation is an American manufacturer of both residential and commercial water heaters and boilers, and the largest manufacturer and marketer of water heaters in North America. It also supplies water treatment and water purification products in the Asian market.

name: Abbott Laboratories
summary: Abbott Laboratories is an American multinational medical devices and health care company with headquarters in Green Oaks, Illinois, United States.

name: AbbVie
summary: AbbVie Inc. is an American pharmaceutical company headquartered in North Chicago, Illinois. It is ranked sixth on the list of largest biomedical companies by revenue. In 2023, the company's seat in Forbes Global 2000 was 74, and rank 89 on the 2024 list.
